content_text: Even though the book said about the world of Wizards and magic, the Harry Potter series contains awful lot of lessons for young people to learn. Firstly, it teaches us important or of friendship. I have read many books but never come across a friendship like that of Harry, Hermione and Ron. These three mosquitoes stuck together throughout the books and never gave up. It taught me the value of good friends. Further, the series of Harry Potter taught me that no one is perfect, everyone has good and evil inside of them. We're the ones who choose what we wish to be. This help me in making better choices and becoming a better human being. We see how the most flawed characters like Snape had goodness inside him. Similarly how.
